No sir. But I haue heard shee is diseas'd with Melancholly;
and if she should proue mad too, like my old Lady, I were
then as farre to seeke as ere I was.

Right. Shee do's but hold off till then, and that wilfully;
because shee feares it is for Constances loue onely, that her
Husband desires the Divorce.

